The paper describes a system for automating the design of predictive modeling pipelines tailored for clinical prognosis using machine learning. The paper specifically mentions the use of Bayesian optimization and meta-learning, which are commonly used in the sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The application of the system is in the field of healthcare, specifically in cardiovascular patient care, which could fall under the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) or clinical informatics (cs.CE). The system also automatically explains its predictions, which could involve natural language processing (cs.CL).
